"title": "5965: temperament",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5965",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A person's disposition, especially as shown in mental or emotional responses. God's people should be of an even temperament.</p>\n<h2>God's people should be of even temperament</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:32\">PRO 16:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1-Titus2:14\">TIT 2:1–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Even temperament is a requirement for church leadership</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:2-1Tim3:3\">1TI 3:2–3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:8-1Tim3:9\">1TI 3:8–3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:11\">1TI 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:7-Titus1:9\">TIT 1:7–1:9</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people who had an unpleasant temperament</h2>\n<h3>Saul</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:23\">1SA 16:23</a></strong> <em>Violent mood swings and bad temper were signs of mental instability in Saul.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:14-1Sam16:16\">1SA 16:14–16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:6-1Sam18:15\">1SA 18:6–18:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:4-1Sam20:7\">1SA 20:4–20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:24-1Sam20:33\">1SA 20:24–20:33</a></p>\n<h3>Nabal the Carmelite</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:17\">1SA 25:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:2-1Sam25:11\">1SA 25:2–25:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:36-1Sam25:38\">1SA 25:36–25:38</a></p>",
